          is called the <term>linear map defined by</term> <m>A</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </definition>

    <p>
      Thus, matrices do not merely store numbers. They also describe transformations of vectors.
    </p>

    <example xml:id="ex-rotation-matrix">
      <title>Rotation in <m>\mathbb{R}^2</m> as a Linear Map</title>
      <p>
        A rotation about the origin through an angle <m>\alpha</m> is described by the matrix
        <me>
          A=
          \begin{pmatrix}
            \cos\alpha &amp; -\sin\alpha \\
            \sin\alpha &amp; \cos\alpha
          \end{pmatrix}.
        </me>
      </p>
